Life history.— One specimen was a ripe male of 116 mm . All other specimens examined were females, the largest was the holotype of 152 mm , a ripe female. The smallest female with yolked eggs was 149 mm (
UW 119817
). At least two sizes of eggs were present in ripe females: yolked eggs were 3.5 mm in diameter and smaller white eggs had diameters of 0.5– 1.5 mm .
